items.title: A blast at a Turkish armament factory kills at least 12 people
items.description: An explosion at an armament factory in northwest Turkey left at least 12 dead and four injured Tuesday morning

items.title: Only 1 hospital in northern Gaza now able to provide services, say officials
items.description: Health officials say there is just one hospital left providing humanitarian aid services in northern Gaza amid the ongoing Israel-Hamas war.

items.title: Bill Clinton hospitalized with fever, in 'good spirits': Spokesperson
items.description: Former President Bill Clinton has been hospitalized after developing a fever, a spokesperson said Monday.

items.title: WATCH:  Santa Cruz wharf partially collapses amid high surf warning along California coast
items.description: Part of the Santa Cruz Wharf collapsed Monday after being battered by waves amid a high surf warning along the California coast.
